<segment id="76" parent="77" relname="circumstance">where Vg represents the phase voltage of the host grid ,</segment>
<segment id="77" parent="1076" relname="span">Vmg represents phase voltage within the microgrid .</segment>
<segment id="78" parent="1078" relname="span">Similarly , Xn signifies needed switched inductive reactance</segment>
<segment id="79" parent="78" relname="circumstance">while In signifies current flow across Xn .</segment>
